The paper focuses on using Linked Open Data (LOD) for recommender systems, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning models such as Factorization Machines (FMs) also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of data management techniques such as SPARQL Endpoint, which is related to database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different approaches for top N recommendations, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
